Reinforcement  of skills acquired during the Academic Writing course. Writing practice in different academic genres, adaptation of texts prior to article publishing, communication with the editor. Preparation of article manuscript for translation. The academic article will be published in the Department of Native Crafts' series Studia vernacula or elsewhere. The article can be based on previous research work or a master's thesis in the making. 
The students should keep a diary according to the rules of the practice course and present a written practice report  where they comment and reflect on the practice as a whole as well as the manuscript creation, technical and cooperation aspects and time consumption.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with efficient and authoritative skills in academic writing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the students should 1) be able to express themselves in an academically correct manner in questions relating to their specialty; 2) be able to efficiently and correctly refer to their chosen system of reference;   3) be able to adapt their academic texts to the article to be published and cooperate with the editor;  4) be able to review the research work of other students; 5) be able to prepare Estonian texts for translation and supportively cooperate with the translator.
